      • inverse

        public boolean inverse​(PointF point,
                       GeoPoint geo,
                       IGeometryModel model)
        Transforms the specified screen coordinate into LLA via a ray intersection against the specified geometry.
        Parameters:
        point - The screen coordinate
        geo - If non-null, stores the result
        model - The geometry, defined in the projected coordinate space
        Returns:
        The LLA point at the specified screen coordinate or null if no intersection with the geometry could be computed.

        AABB intersection test with the viewing frustum.
        Parameters:
        model -
        mbbMinX - The minimum longitude of the MBB
        mbbMinY - The minimum latitude of the MBB
        mbbMinZ - The minimum altitude (HAE) of the MBB
        mbbMaxX - The maximum longitude of the MBB
        mbbMaxY - The maximum latitude of the MBB
        mbbMaxZ - The maximum altitude (HAE) of the MBB

        Bounding sphere intersection test with the viewing frustum.
        Parameters:
        model -
        latitude - Latitude of the center of the sphere
        longitude - Longitude of the center of the sphere
        hae - Altitude of the center of the sphere, meters HAE
        radiusMeters - The radius of the sphere, in meters
        Returns:
